 :tx/rationale "Create task: DAEMON-1 (REOPENED): Incremental Store — Store::apply_tx(&mut self, datoms: &[Datom]) for O(k) in-place mutation (INV-STORE-001, ADR-STORE-005, ADR-STORE-019). BACKGROUND: Original t-0a1b5c4e was falsely auto-closed by harvest reconciliation with 0% criteria_confidence (reconciliation bug — spec_coverage alone is insufficient). The task is NOT implemented. Currently Store is immutable — from_datoms() rebuilds all 5 indexes from scratch in O(n). The daemon needs to apply transactions incrementally without full rebuild. APPROACH: (1) Add pub fn apply_tx(&mut self, datoms: &[Datom]) to Store. For each datom: insert into self.datoms (BTreeSet), push to entity_index[d.entity], push to attribute_index[d.attribute]. (2) If Value::Ref: push to vaet_index[target_entity]. (3) If Op::Assert: push to avet_index[(attr,val)]. (4) CRITICAL — Op::Retract handling: for retract datoms, do NOT add to avet_index. Update live_view by removing the (entity,attr) entry if the retracted value matches the current live value, then scanning entity_datoms for the next-latest assertion. (5) Update frontier: for each datom, if datom.tx > frontier[datom.tx.agent], advance. (6) Schema update: if any datom has attribute starting with :db/, rebuild schema via Schema::from_datoms (rare path, ok to be O(n)). (7) ISOMORPHISM INVARIANT: for any store S and set of datoms D, S.clone().apply_tx(D) must produce identical state to Store::from_datoms(S.datom_set().union(D)). This is the fundamental correctness property. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Isomorphism property test passes (100 proptest iterations). (B) apply_tx is O(k) where k = |datoms| for assert-only transactions. (C) All 5 indexes + live_view consistent after apply_tx. (D) Retraction correctly updates live_view (removes value, falls back to previous). (E) Schema updated when :db/* attributes present. (F) Frontier monotonically advances. (G) Empty transaction is a no-op. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/store.rs. TRACES-TO: INV-STORE-001, ADR-STORE-005, ADR-STORE-019."
